## Journal

The knowledge sets and journal live in an Obsidian vault. Interact with the vault
through the `obsidian` MCP server (search, read, and write notes) — do NOT write vault
files directly on disk, so edits stay coherent with Obsidian's editor and index.

The project journal is in the vault at `{{ journal_vault_path }}/`, one note per
{{ journal_write_type }} named `<date>.md` using the date format `{{ journal_date_format }}`.
Today's note is `{{ journal_vault_path }}/<today>.md`.

At the end of each session, create or update today's note via the `obsidian` MCP server
and prepend a brief summary of what was accomplished (insert it before existing content,
preserving anything already there).
